President Obama has declared a state of emergency in New Jersey and ordered federal aid to help with the aftermath of Hurricane Sandy. The declaration allows the Department of Homeland Security and FEMA to coordinate relief efforts and provide assistance to save lives and protect property. FEMA is authorized to mobilize resources and equipment to alleviate the impacts of the emergency, with 75 percent of funding provided by the federal government. Elizabeth Turner has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area.